elton ct june   apply add to cart about the opportunity as a senior product manager you will work to innovate and lead in the mailing and communications space with the expanding role of digital communications we are growing existing businesses and launching new ones to ensure our clients can communicate the digital landscape evolves the senior product manager is responsible for owning the clients’ endtoend experience driving their products from concept to delivery and being accountable for the delivery of planned global business results your career with pitney bowes will help you succeed by providing a competitive salary and benefits extensive training and a high profile career path for successful performers this position is located in shelton connecticut build deploy bridge grow in this role you’ll join our smallmedium business smb solutions team and report to the director smb software  services you will be responsible for understand our customers’ needs and motivations and champion the “voice of the customer” internally build maintain and drive a clear and prioritized roadmap for delivering a product that maintains a dominant position in the marketplace may include pursuing new channel strategies partner relationships and models or internal development understand and analyze the market including industry trends the position of our competitors and potential opportunities and threats to our strategy define a strategy to stay ahead of the competition and optimize our market opportunity demonstrated success in pl management and being accountable in driving the attainment of planned global revenue and profit for assigned portfolio proven experience launching and growing commercially successful webbased applications or saas offerings experience leading crossfunctional teams to deliver results experience defining relevant success metrics and using data to influence decisions includes developing and presenting business cases and tracking postlaunch performance ability to “dig in” and understand the root cause of a problem define potential options for solving the problem and make decisions for both the short and long terms excellent interpersonal and communication skills and an ability to communicate complicated ideas in a clear and simple way both internal and externally qualifications bachelor’s degree mba preferred  years of experience in product management managing software and services through the entire lifecycle experience working with thirdparty partners proven experience developing launching and growing including pl responsibility commercially successful software and services especiallywebbased applications or software experience with saas applications is highly desirable experience with addressing software and related us and canadian postal regulations is highly desirable the team within our smallmedium business smb solutions team we provide a full range of mailing equipment and postage meters maintenance and support services and supplies that enable our clients to efficiently create mail and evidence postage we segment our smb solutions business between our north america operations comprising the us and canadian businesses and our international operations we are a leading provider of postage meters and have approximately one million meters installed pitney bowes is an equal employment opportunityaffirmative action employer that values diversity and inclusiveness in the workplace mfveteransindividuals with disabilitieslgbt are encouraged to apply all interested individuals must apply online individuals with disabilities who cannot apply via our online application should refer to the alternate application options via our individuals with disabilities link jobs that may interest youprogram managerwhite river junction vtfinance manager – project accountant data migration – system implementationhatfield englandlogistics associate  nd shift pmammilwaukee wion site electro mechanical technician  mail processing equipment repair m