nbach president and ceo michael monahan coo products franking machines geolocation software mail sorters crm software location intelligence customer information management ecommerce solutions revenue us billion  number of employees   website wwwpitneybowescom former pitney bowes headquarters in stamford pitney bowes inc is an american provider of global ecommerce solutions shipping and mailing products location intelligence customer engagement and customer information management solutions based in stamford connecticut the company has approximately  employees worldwide it was one of  existing firms that had been members of the sp  since its creation in  other major us centers of operation include danbury connecticut shelton connecticut troy new york and lanham maryland contents  history  research and technology  significant acquisitions  credit ratings and revenue  references  further reading  external links historyedit in  arthur pitney patented his first doublelocking handcranked postagestamping machine and with patent attorney eugene a rummler founded the pitney postal machine company in  english emigrant and founder of the universal stamping machine company walter bowes began providing stampcanceling machines to the united states postal service bowes moved his operations to stamford in  a rapid increase in mail volume in  made the post office more receptive to metered mail and pitney subsequently traveled to meet bowes on march   the united states house of representatives passed a bill authorizing mechanical stamps on firstclass mail and on april   the two companies merged to form the pitney bowes postage meter company with the goal of producing a machine that would combine pitneys doublelocking counter with bowes system for wrapping postage payment postmarking and cancellation the united states post office approved their postage meter on august   between  and  the government collected  in postage from the first commercial installations of  meters pitney bowes also began to sell their products internationally in  walter h wheeler jr was named president and chairman of the board and would lead the company over the next three decades in the s wheeler boycotted a hotel when it refused to register one black salesperson championing a spirit of diversity that still exists today writing pitney bowes worksites will reflect the communities in which we operate during the s the national urban league recognized pitney bowes for its leadership in providing job opportunities to african americans during world war ii pitneybowes received an armynavy ‘e’ award denoting excellence in production of crucially needed instruments of war february   the company went public on the new york stock exchange in  subsequently pitney bowes was named to the sp  when this benchmark index was created in  and joined the fortune  in  in  pitney bowes acquired the monarch marking system company which would produce the first barcode equipment for retail trade use to better provide financing options for their existing and prospective customers the pitney bowes credit corporation was formed in  pitney bowes would continue to grow this line of business launching the pitney bowes bank in  throughout the s and s the firm expanded offering copy machines and facsimile machines a suite of management services and entering new markets such as japan during this period pitney bowes acquired dictaphone and kept the dictation machine manufacturer as a wholly owned but independent subsidiary until the unit was sold in  in the s pitney bowes continued to innovate in the field of digital technologies and software introducing the addressright address  barcode printer  the first inline weighing and metering system  the first secure digital postage meter  the first ink jet postage meter  and the digital document deliver d platform  which provides message management via hard copy web email and fax since  pitney bowes invested  billion in  acquisitions primarily in software and services businesses including mapinfo group  software psi group and imagitas the software portfolio has been largely grouped into an operating division called pitney bowes software in august  the firm announced that it sold its world headquarters building in stamford ct one elmcroft road but it would remain in the same city and move to  stamford square summer street the relocation is expected to be complete by the summer of  on october   pitney bowes sold its management services division pbms to private equity firm apollo global management for  million in cash the proceeds of which would be principally to pay down debt pbms has since been renamed novitex enterprise solutions on january   pitney bowes unveiled a new brand strategy and logo that supposedly better reflects the companys selfproclaimed role as a technology company that powers billions of physical and digital transactions across the connected and borderless world of commerce  research and technologyedit pitney bowes’ intellectual property portfolio includes more than  patents worldwide in areas such as ticketing cellular phone payment shipping laser printing encryption and mail production and processing the intellectual property owners ipo association has consistently ranked pitney bowes in the top  companies receiving us patents six of these patents are held by retired executive chairman michael j critelli murray d martin a former chairman president and chief executive officer is named on two significant acquisitionsedit since  pitney bowes has invested  billion in  acquisitions primarily in software and services businesses  maponics  portrait software plc henleyonthames england provides customercentric solutions that combine advanced customer analytics with inbound and outbound campaign managementclarification needed  mapinfo troy ny provides location intelligence solutions  digital cement toronto canada provides customer relationship management strategy and services  print inc bellevue wa provides print management solutions  advertising audit service aas and pmh mi offers webbased tools for customized promotional mail and marketing collateral and designs and manages customer and channel performance solutions  ibis consulting inc ri provides electronic discovery services and solutions to law firms and corporate clients  emtex ltd england provides software and services that simplify document production and centrally manage multivendor and multisite printer operations  imagitas waltham ma provides marketing services that use the mail to help companies connect with hard to reach consumers including new movers through my move  compulit inc mi provides litigation support services to law firms and corporate clients  international mail express imex ny consolidates letters and flatsized mail headed to international addresses  group  software inc lanham md provides software that enhances mailing efficiency data quality and customer communications  kilburn office automation limited acquired the mailing business division for a direct entry into the lucrative indian market pitney bowes was advised by nitin banerjee and nitesh bhasin  ddd company md provides fulfillment services secure mail process messenger services logistics support and record and information management  psi group inc omaha ne provides presort mail services  danka services international dsi london england provides imaging equipment and related services parts and supplies in approximately  countries  secap sa france provides a range of mail processing and paper handling equipment for low to midvolume mailers  bell  howell’s international mmt london england markets and services highend mail processing sorting and servicerelated products credit ratings and revenueedit in february  the credit rating for pitney bowes international holdings was lowered by fitch ratings from bbb to bbb the ratings agency said its main concern was the downward trajectory of pitney bowes revenue and added that they have a negative outlook in march  moodys assigned a longterm rating of baa to the companys proposed  million senior unsecured notes due  and reiterated their stable outlook on pbi moodys cited an improvement in the companys operating margin to around  from about  historically following the sale of its labor intensive management services business and an operational restructuring which could yield annual cost savings of up to  million by   in february  pitney bowes announced that its full year  revenue was b a decline of  over the previous year referencesedit  a b pbi profile  pitney bowes inc common stock stock yahoo finance  retrieved november     sp releases list of  companies in the sp  since  prnewswirecom march   retrieved march     black enterprise july   the story of pitneybowes william cahn   pitney bowes selling dictaphone chicago tribune   stamford advocate august    stamford advocate march     winter triangle  pitney bowes choses  stamford square ashforthcom  retrieved    pitney bowes newsroom  pitney bowes completes sale of its management services business to apollo funds for  million newspbcom retrieved    httpwwwnovitexcompdfsnewsreleasespressreleasepbmsbecomesnovitexenterpirsesolutionspdf  httpnewspbcomarticledisplaycfmarticleid  missing or empty title help  ibm pitneybowes others give free green patents reuters retrieved on   digitalcementcom  imagitascom  mymovecom  fitch lowers pitney bowes credit ratings to bbb yahoo news    moodys rates pitney bowes new senior unsecured notes baa outlook stable moodyscom  retrieved    pitney bowes newsroom  pitney bowes announces full year and fourth quarter  financial results newspbcom retrieved   further readingedit cahn william  the story of pitneybowes new york harper  brothers  external linksedit wikimedia commons has media related to pitney bowes pitney bowes home page business data for pitney bowes google finance yahoo finance reuters sec filings retrieved from httpsenwikipediaorgwindexphptitlepitneybowesoldid categories compani